                    },
                    "company": "Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam (VU Amsterdam)",
                    "description": "For my second internship as a MSc student in Biological Sciences, I investigated competition and cooperation between arbuscular mycorrhizal fungi and their hosts plants, at the VU University in Amsterdam. Supervised by prof. Toby Kiers, I learned to understand below-ground ecosystems, and specifically the interactions between plant roots and soil fungi. In this project, I refined my experimental skills by conducting a large climate-room based controlled experiment, as well as molecular lab skills by performing hyphal staining and qPCR analysis. The results of this project led to a collaborative effort that was published in Fungal Ecology:\n\nKnegt, B., Jansa, J., Franken, O., Engelmoer, D.J.P., Werner, G.D.A., B\u00fccking, H. and E. Toby Kiers. (2016). Host plant quality mediates competition between arbuscular mycorrhizal fungi. Fungal Ecology 20: 233-240.\nLink: http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1754504814001354",
